A bus drove through the boundary wall and into the front a house on Canehaven Drive in Caneside, Phoenix on Wednesday morning. Fortunately, Reaction Unit South Africa (RUSA) said, no one was injured. RUSA said their response ream arrived at the scene just before 7 am and found that the bus had driven into the house. “The driver of the bus was the only occupant in the vehicle at the time. The homeowner was inside the house at the time of the incident and was not injured” Details leading up to the accident have not been established at this stage, said RUSA. 